<div mc:edit="std_content00">
<h4 class="h4">In This Issue:</h4>
<ul style="font-weight: bold">
<li>Three ways to make sure you sell an investment when the time is right…</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic">“How I infiltrated this private club reserved for the rich”</span></li>
<li>Unconventional Millionaires banked 235.96% in cumulative gains on six stocks in 2012</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="h3"><img height="15" src="http://www.fsp.co.za/downloads/RSN/images/divider_rs.gif" width="214"></h3>
<p style="text-align: right">10 December 2012</p>
<p>From your <a href="http://newsletters.fsp.co.za/servlet/link/49/7989/50050/78556"><span style="font-style: italic">Unconventional Millionaire</span></a>, Gavin Fourie</p>
<p>Dear <em>Rich Secrets</em> reader,</p>
<p>To keep your investment returns high, you need to go into any investment knowing when you’ll sell.<br>
<br>
This is one of the most difficult problems many investors face.<br>
<br>
Most investors don’t have a plan or a strategy for selling. So it's easy for them to get into trouble.<br>
<br>
One of their biggest obstacles is letting greed prevent them from selling an investment.<br>
<br>
That’s why I’ve developed a simple strategy that gives me a clear signal when to sell an investment.<br>
<br>
And today, I want to share this with you… <br></p>
<h3 class="h3"><img height="15" src="http://www.fsp.co.za/downloads/RSN/images/divider_rs.gif" width="214"></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic">“How I infiltrated this private club reserved for the rich”</span><br>
<br>
Former music teacher reveals 16 secrets to unlock the vaults of the JSE – doubling her investment returns in 3 days…<br>
<br>
“When I say this book changed my life… I’m not joking!<br>
<br>
Not only did I learn the markets in 3 days and manage to keep my job, I’ve also taken the stock market by storm. I finally understand why investing my money is the right thing to do. And all I want to do now is <a href=
"http://newsletters.fsp.co.za/servlet/link/49/7989/50050/78557"><span style="font-weight: bold">make sure you get your hands on this book before it’s too late.”</span></a></p>
<h3 class="h3"><img height="15" src="http://www.fsp.co.za/downloads/RSN/images/divider_rs.gif" width="214"></h3>
<p><br>
<span style="font-weight: bold">Three ways to make sure you sell an investment when the time is right…</span><br style="font-weight: bold">
<span style="font-weight: bold"> </span><br>
<span style="font-weight: bold">#1: Whenever you invest in something, it's important to write down why you invested in the first place</span><br>
 So get out some paper and write down your reasons for investing in it. This could be it was cheap based on its price to earnings or it consistently pays a high dividend.<br>
<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold">#2: Write down when you'll sell the investment</span><br>
Do it on the same piece of paper and at the same time you buy the investment.<br>
You need to do two things:<br></p>
<div style="margin-left: 40px">a.    Write down you maximum loss you’re willing to take. And set a stop loss at this level – and don’t move it lower. Then as your investment increases, you should move the stop loss higher.<br>
<br>
b.    Write down your profit target. When your investment hits this price, you’ll sell. If it doesn’t get there in a specified time, you’ll sell your investment as well.</div>
<p> <br>
<span style="font-weight: bold">#3: You must review your investments.</span><br>
You should do this frequently to make sure the reasons you bought are still valid. If they’re no longer valid, then sell the stock.<br>
<br>
I’ve just sent my <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic"><a href="http://newsletters.fsp.co.za/servlet/link/49/7989/50050/78558" style=
"font-weight: bold">Unconventional Millionaire</a></span> readers their yearly review of the stocks in our portfolio.<br>
<br>
And guess what?<br>
<br>
We’ve banked 235.96% in cumulative gains this year. Because the reason we got in were no longer valid.<br>
<br>
<span style="font-weight: bold">Here’s how my portfolio of stocks have performed this year...</span><br>
<br>
<img alt="" height="280" src="http://newsletters.fsp.co.za/users/assets/3/images/Finance/UCM/RST%20UCM%20Chart.jpg" width="480"><br>
<br>
Our portfolio has had a great performance, to get access to the <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic">Unconventional Millionaire</span> stock selection system and the 11 buy rated stocks <span style="font-weight: bold"><a href=
"http://newsletters.fsp.co.za/servlet/link/49/7989/50050/78559" style="font-weight: bold">click here</a>.</span></p>
<p>To living the millionaire lifestyle now!</p>
<p><br>
<img alt="" height="85" src="http://newsletters.fsp.co.za/users/assets/3/images/Finance/Signatures/Gav%20Sig_10_10_11_small.jpg" width="90"><br>
Gavin Fourie<br>
<a href="http://newsletters.fsp.co.za/servlet/link/49/7989/50050/78560">Your Unconventional Millionaire</a></p>
